  "condition": "Condition.code.coding Maps to a standard concept with domain_id='Observation' (e.g. SNOMED 'Prediabetes', 'Family history of ...').",
  "narrative_md": "Sibling of `Condition__condition_occurrence`. Same staging table (`staging.condition_occurrence`, per-coding fan-out). This edge picks the codings whose `Maps to` target lands in the Observation domain rather than the Condition domain — without it those rows (≈3258 / 4204 on Synthea) would be silently dropped. PK is `hash(Condition.id || '|' || std_concept_id)` so different codings of the same Condition that resolve to different std concepts get distinct rows.",
  "fields": [
